					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm doubtful that $C001 changes the IRQ counter at all.  It probably works more like how the APU hardware works -- it sets a "reset" flag, then when the IRQ counter is clocked, it checks the state of that reset flag before decrementing the counter.
<br />
<br />This especially makes sense when you look at RAMBO-1's "reset with X+1" quirk.  RAMBO-1 probably has the same reset flag, and merely checks for zero before the decrement rather than after it.
<br />
<br />/me adds to list of things to change in his docs</div>

